raw_data.title: Senior Attorney
raw_data.description:
The Senior Attorney must be a licensed attorney with experience in private law firm, in-house corporate office, and/or government agency. The Senior Attorney has in depth experience and expertise in administrative law, procurement, contract law, business law, commercial law, corporate law, employment law, real estate, banking and finance, intellectual property, due diligence, and/or investigative analysis, with experience and expertise in related litigation, trial practice, appeals, and/or transactions. The Senior Attorney is a graduate of an ABA accredited law school (Juris Doctorate degree, which is equivalent to PhD degree in law) and members of bars of one or more state or the District of
Columbia.

raw_data.title: Program Manager
raw_data.description: Overall responsibility for management of contract, program, and/or multiple projects, including handling planning, management, deliverables, and meeting client expectations. Ensures all contract obligations are fulfilled, quality standards are met, and services are performed and delivered, within expected time frames and budget. Key responsibilities include: managing program, projects, and tasks; managing personnel; formulating work plans; ensuring deliverables; managing funds and resources; and serving as point of contact with stakeholders and program staff.

raw_data.title: Deputy Program Manager
raw_data.description: Assists Program Manager in supporting management of contract, program, and/or multiple projects, including planning, management, handling deliverables, and meeting client expectations. Assists Program Manager to ensure that all contract obligations are fulfilled, quality standards are met, and services are performed and delivered, within expected time frames and budget. Key responsibilities include: assist in managing programs, projects, and tasks; to assist in managing personnel; to assist in carry out work plans; to assist in ensuring deliverables; to assist in managing funds and resources; and to assist in communication with stakeholders and program staff.

raw_data.title: Project Manager II
raw_data.description: Responsible for managing specific project or projects, including handling planning, management, deliverables, and meeting client expectations. Ensures all contract obligations are fulfilled, quality standards are met, and services are performed and delivered, within expected time frames and budget. Plan, organize, control, direct and manage tasks and actions to meet target objectives. Plan and implement actions by team to deliver and meet quality requirements. Direct project team personnel, manage cost and schedule, ensure contract compliance, and serve as customer point of contact

raw_data.title: Project Manager I
raw_data.description: Responsible for managing a specific project or task, including assisting with planning, management, deliverables, and meeting client expectations. Assist in ensuring all contract obligations are fulfilled, quality standards are met, and services are performed and delivered, within expected time frames and budget. Assist to plan, organize, control, direct and manage tasks and actions to meet target objectives. Assist to implement actions by team to deliver and meet quality requirements. Assist with personnel, cost, schedule, contract compliance, and customer support.

raw_data.title: Senior Analyst
raw_data.description:
Responsible for delivering very high level of advice, analysis, research, guidance, management, or technical support for management, organizational, financial, technical, or business efforts. Analyze complex issues, research operation and processes, define requirements, monitor, and identify issues, design and recommend solutions, recommend resource allocation, review and analyze operations, business, and technical processes, develop and monitor tasks and projects, manage teams and resources, and provide client assistance.
Provides assistance in training, logistics, management, budget and finance, security, configuration management, data management, business and process management, program control, technical processes, and/or manpower planning.

raw_data.title: Analyst

Responsible for delivering high level of advice, analysis, research, guidance, management, or technical support for 
client’s management, organizational, financial, technical, or business efforts. Analyze complex issues, research operation and processes, define requirements, monitor, and identify issues, design and recommend solutions, recommend resource allocation, review and analyze operations, business, and technical processes, develop and monitor tasks and projects, manage teams and resources, and provide client assistance.
Provides assistance in training, logistics, management, budget and finance, security, configuration management, data management, business and process management, program control, technical processes, and/or manpower planning. May work independently or under the supervision of Senior Analyst.

raw_data.title: Senior Consultant
raw_data.description: Provides senior consulting expertise to address complex needs and challenges. Serves as a senior-level consultant on project or program, develops work plans, solutions, strategies, and modeling. Demonstrates ability to organize, analyze, interpret, and evaluate situations, options, industry trends, policies, and regulates to translate finding into solutions to serve program/project goals.  Supports clients’ management, organizational and business efforts. Analyzes and interprets complex sets of information to provide value to further client objectives.

Demonstrates ability to organize, analyze, interpret, and evaluate situations, options, industry trends, policies, and regulates to translate finding into solutions to serve 
Program/project goals.  Support clients’ management, organizational and business efforts. Analyzes and interprets complex sets of information to provide value to further client objectives.

raw_data.title: Administrative Assistant II
raw_data.description:
Possesses proficiency in written and oral communication. Able to work in general office tasks, including records maintenance, scheduling, and drafting and editing documents and presentations. Conducts general research and compiles data, updates files and records, and responds to requests and questions. Organizes and creates files. Schedules and organizes activities, meetings, calls, and appointments.
Prepares expense reports. Organizes and maintains project related files. Provides general office support including answering phones, photocopying records, faxing documents, and entering data.

Conducts general research and compiles data, updates files and records, and responds to requests and questions. Organizes and creates files. Schedules and organizes activities, meetings, calls, and appointments.
Prepares expense reports. Organizes and maintains project related files. Provides general office support including answering phones, photocopying records, faxing documents, and entering data.

raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert
raw_data.description:
Provides technical, managerial, and administrative direction for problem definition, analysis, requirements development, and implementation for complex concepts, practices, and procedures in the subject matter area. Makes recommendations and advises on system improvements, optimization or maintenance efforts in the following specialties: administrative, procurement, contract, business, commercial, corporate, real estate, banking and finance, intellectual property, due diligence, investigative fields, information systems, architecture, automation, communications protocols, risk management/analysis, life- cycle management, acquisitions, management consulting, business processes, logistics, and/or scientific discipline.
Demonstrated exceptional written and oral communications skills, including giving formal presentations.
